I like the Big Fish HO games because they are high quality, they are very 
long, and they still put them on sale in the store, which some of the other 
HO games have stopped doing. This was another good game, but I'm taking 1/2 
star off because the map exclamation point was glitchy and didn't always 
point to the right scene. I'm also taking 1/2 star off for making the 
single most used button in the game, the map button, tiny and hard and 
frustrating to press. It was a constant irritation throughout the game. 
Otherwise, another high-quality very long game that provided good 
entertainment value.
